  "text": "Modern anonymity systems date to Chaum's Mix-Net design [CITATION_1] . Chaum proposed hiding the correspondence between sender and recipient by wrapping messages in layers of public-key cryptography, and relaying them through a path composed of \"mixes.\" Each mix in turn decrypts, delays, and re-orders messages before relaying them onward.",
